coming aware of all the pits and falls of the online investment industry, which have cost tens of thousands of dollars for beginners like you. So, if you&rsquo;re just starting out on HYIPS investment plans, we suggest that you find the best brokers to manage asset for you. They&rsquo;ll help spot best facilities as well as best trading environment for you to get started immediately, without burning your pockets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not skip this step because it will not only prevent you from making commonly made mistakes by beginner investors that have cost them fortune, but it will also help you make a correct decisions while selecting a brokerage firm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use online broker checker tools to find genuine stock and Forex traders.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you have any questions regarding HYIP investment plan or don&rsquo;t know how to get started, quickly?&nbsp;<a href="http://sharehyip.com/contact">Contact us</a>&nbsp;to get started immediately and start earning high RETURNS from your first few investments.</p>', '2014-03-26 16:13:29', '2014-03-26 16:13:29'),
(47, '5 Easy Ways to Protect Yourself from Investing on SCAM HYIP programs', '5-easy-ways-to-protect-yourself-from-investing-on-scam-hyip-programs', 2, '<p>HYIP are great way to earn passive income, but, as you must be aware, Internet is crammed with everything &ndash; the good, the bad, and the ugly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are great high yield investment programs that could make your good amount of money, but if you&rsquo;re not careful, you could also lost all your hard-earned money through fraudulent programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So, if you were thinking about making profits (money) through one of the HYIP found on the Internet, but not sure how to &lsquo;avoid&rsquo; junk and scams, and invest right into a genuine program that will make your money, you need to read this investment guide.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Over the past several years, HYIP program has gained such popularity among Internet users that all types of website have sprouted. While most of them are actually &lsquo;paying&rsquo; HYIP program, there are still plenty of &lsquo;fake&rsquo; scam HYIPs too.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You need to be prepared before investing a dime on these online investment programs. Protecting your hard-earned money must be your number 1 priority. If you do NOT, you can no longer invest. Does that make sense?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With that said, let&rsquo;s look at few common tips that you, as an investor, can follow to start protecting your finances as well as your Personal Information so that unauthorized people cannot access and abuse it:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Top tips on protecting yourself from SCAM HYIP program:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Prevention#1: Install anti-virus and firewall program on your devices.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re investing on HYIPs using your computers, laptops, tablets, and mobiles, we highly recommend you to you protect your system by installing anti-virus programs and firewalls and keep malicious and phishing programs at bay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also &lsquo;scan&rsquo; your devices using anti-virus program and remove malicious programs and content. Remember that some &lsquo;.exe&rsquo; files are designed to scan and grab sensitive data (credit card number and account login information) from your devices by an unknown user over the Internet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To stop this, install anti-virus program, update it frequently, and block unwanted sites using firewall. Use a safe browser such as Chrome to conduct online transactions on HYIP sites.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Prevention#2: Uninstall Unnecessary Add-ons on Your Devices.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>During installing anti-virus and firewalls on your devices, &lsquo;uncheck&rsquo; unnecessary add-ons you may NOT need. For example, you do not need Internet SPEED BOOSTER, or SPEEDBIT search engine, or Download Manager to improve your system performance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not install them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These unnecessary programs will only create additional hassles on your system and browsers (more entries for the user).</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Prevention#3: Make your WIFI connections secure.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re using a wireless connection to access the Internet, you need to be EXTRA careful while investing on online investment sites for several reasons. First, understand that FREE WIFI connections are accessible from any place these days and you might be tempted to use it to make online investment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HUGE Mistake!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Although having a FREE WIFI connection is convenient and easy, but making online investment through it could cost you plenty of money. How?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Well, if you&rsquo;re not living in the caves, you&rsquo;d probably know that these so-called FREE WIFI facilities have UNSECURE network and investing through them could mean putting your hard-earned money right into the hands of potential online hackers (cybercriminals) lurking behind the scenes. These people can easily enter into the WIFI network, use their complex programs to gain access to your system, and &lsquo;scan&rsquo; through your device to grab your credit card and account login information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To stop this from happening, make sure that you deposit and withdraw your money/earnings on a secure WIFI. Use anti-virus programs like Avast to prevent malicious codes entering your system.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Prevention#4: Check your trader/brokers.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you&rsquo;ve taken care of &lsquo;cybercriminals,&rsquo; it&rsquo;s time to weed out those traders and brokers who charge you &lsquo;hidden fees&rsquo; for offering their financial services to you.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Prevention #5: Know the risks and rewards of each trading.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you&rsquo;ve chosen an investment plan to invest on, do not jump in to deposit your hard-earned money yet. Do a basic analysis of the asset first to know its pros and cons (risks and rewards) before investing on it. This way not only you&rsquo;ll be leveraging on your risks, but also get high ROIs for your time, effort, and money.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Conclusion &ndash; Protect Yourself from HYIP Scams</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you have pressing questions regarding getting started on online investment programs such as HYIPs? If yes, contact us or email us at&nbsp;<a href="mailto:sharehyip@gmail.com">sharehyip@gmail.com</a>&nbsp;and get unbiased and genuine investment strategies that actually WORKS!</p>', '2014-04-03 19:36:15', '2014-04-03 19:36:15'),
(48, 'Top 5 Investing Scams That YOU MUST AVOID', 'top-5-investing-scams-that-you-must-avoid', 2, '<p>In recent years, stock market has been showing signs of gaining it&rsquo;s lost track.&nbsp; However, for many investors, this recovery isn&rsquo;t sufficient. They are still searching for quicker ways to yield higher profits and bolster their investment portfolios.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But the problems lies in the fact that most high yield investment programs (HYIPs), almost 90%&nbsp; of them, are downright frauds. Most critics think HYIPs are similar to Ponzi schemes, crammed with &lsquo;scam&rsquo; artists only after investors hard-earned money.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition to newbies, investment fraudsters are also targeting senior investors. In recent years, seniors are complaining their retirement accounts and earnings are slowly dwindling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Among all these scams making the rounds later in the Internet, every investors major concern is the same &ndash; how to spot scam artists before making an online investment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are top 5 scam investment programs that you should be aware of (ranked in terms of its seriousness and prevalence):</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><em>#1: Ponzi Schemes</em></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Ponzi scheme was named after Charles Ponzi, a fraudster from the early 1920s who swindled over $10 million dollar from investors by promising over 40 percent profit share. Countless other scam artists has been copying his formula by promising higher returns&nbsp; to attract investors and use their money to pay their current investors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whenever they&rsquo;re inquired for the failure of their system, Ponzi ,,scammers,, will often blame the government.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><em>#2: Promissory Notes</em></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Insurance agents sell these short-term debt instruments to investors promising higher return, up-to 15% monthly profit share, with little or no risked involved. These companies are little-known and most likely non-existent.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><em>#3: Affinity Fraud</em></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Scammers are also taking a lot of advantage from people who have tendency to trust others who share similar interest. These scam artists build trust and then steal their life long savings without their victim&rsquo;s knowing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These swindling programs may including handing out &lsquo;gifts&rsquo; at churches and tempting people to invest in scam foreign exchange trades.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><em>#4: Unlicensed Individuals</em></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Scam artists also tempt independent insurance agents to sell investments to people who do not know a lot about them. For example, the person in charge of this scam ask &lsquo;unlicensed&rsquo; agents to convince newbie investors by promising higher returns with little or no risk at all.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you (an investor) are approached by any independent agent, you must do your due diligence to check their credibility first. Call state securities and ask whether the agent is licensed. Next, ask whether the company offering investment plan is registered. If the answer is &lsquo;yes,&rsquo; do NOT rush investing in the program though. Review the product by remaining skeptic as you&rsquo;d do for any other investment types.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><em>#5: Internet Fraud</em></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Internet fraud is a BOOMING business for many &lsquo;scam&rsquo; artists. In November, last year, local, state, federal and foreign law-enforcement officers conducted an Operation Cyber Sweep that made 125 arrests, identified more than 125,000 victims who were losing an estimated $100 million.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Internet is the best &ndash; fast and cheap &ndash; medium for these &lsquo;scam&rsquo; artists to reach out to millions of potential victims.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many officials against cyber theft are warning potential investors to be wary of infamous Nigerian 419 scam, saying that they must ignore emails and offers from people in need of help to deposit money in overseas bank accounts. If you get these type of e- mail, simply hit the &lsquo;delete&rsquo; button. Stop being conned.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Read our&nbsp;<a href="http://sharehyip.com/blog">blog</a>&nbsp;for learn more HYIP tips and tricks.</p>', '2014-04-25 06:19:06', '2014-04-25 06:19:06'),
(49, 'How Do HYIPs Invest YOUR Hard-Earned Money?', 'how-do-hyips-invest-your-hard-earned-money', 2, '<p>HYIPs, high yield investment programs, is an investment program/scheme that is designed to offer HIGH RETURNS to its investors in least amount of time. HYIPs is considered to be one of the most profitable money making ventures available for everyone, including both first-time investors and industry veterans. Investors can earn anywhere between 5-200% interest of their initial investment every month.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As with any other speculative (risky) businesses, all these profits that an investor make is most dependent on the risks they are willing to make. In other words, higher the risks, higher the returns or losses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HOW do HYIPs invest your hard-earned money?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most HYIPs do NOT go in-detail on how they invest their investor&rsquo;s money. But in general, all HYIPs are involved in capital management, which is all about managing investment amount as well as capital expenditures that are needed to make the business thrive.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HYIPs manage investor&rsquo;s capital through various modes, including FOREX trading, sports betting, sports betting, stock exchange, metal trading among others.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><em>#1: FOREX Trading:</em></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Forex trading involves buying and selling of currencies (foreign exchange).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With over $1.5 trillion daily turn over, FOREX is considered to have the most volume among all other types of markets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In FOREX, US dollar is used as the base currency against which other currencies are traded. Moreover, investors can cash in and withdraw their investments in less time and with fairer market price than any other market, which makes it &nbsp;the most liquid market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>FOREX trading is non-monopolistic, meaning no single entity has the ability to control and monopolize because of its HUGE&nbsp; volume.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not to mention, FOREX trading runs 24 hours a day, 5 days a week, letting investors invest any time and reaping great returns from the worldwide developments while local market is sleeping.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Just as with other types of investment, currency markets are highly speculative and unpredictable, which also means higher returns/losses. That is one of the reasons why FOREX and currency market in general is considered to be such a lucrative money making venture for may investors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many HYIPs you see in the market exploit this highly profit and money making nature of FOREX to generate maximum yield for their investors.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><em>#2: STOCK Exchange:</em></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Besides FOREX trading, most HYIPs invest their investor&rsquo;s hard earned money through STOCK exchange/market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>STOCK market may seem a viable option for many newbie investors as it is more structured as well as organized market, which basically means lower risks for investors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Members trade in stocks, common stocks, and bonds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In STOCK exchange, members trade as agents/brokers or as principals/traders/dealers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are different ways you can carry out stock exchange trading. One of the ways is to trade stocks on a auction basis. Secondly, you could hire a stock expert who specialize in a particular stock. Thirdly, you could get help from stock brokers who buy and sell stocks to dealers and traders in a particular stock type.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><em>#3: SPORTS betting/gambling:</em></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Many HYIPs also invest their investor&rsquo;s money into sports betting/gambling market to yield higher returns for their members. In sports gambling, members make earnings from a predicted result/ outcomes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The legality, acceptance, and the mechanics of sports gambling differs from country to country. In North America, for example, the only sports that is allowed betting is horse racing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the other hand, in many European countries, sports betting is strictly monitored and regulated, although it&rsquo;s not considered to be illegal there.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><em>#4: Metal Trading</em></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>In Metal trading, precious metals such as gold and silver are traded. In addition to gold and silver, palladium and platinum are also traded.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><em>#5: Virtual Currencies, or e-Currencies.</em></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>HYIPs also trade using e-currencies or virtual currencies through the Internet.&nbsp; In fact, many investors from around the world have been able to participate in online HYIPs and are making instant earnings. In addition to accepting large amount of investors, online HYIPs also accepts small investments, making it extremely easy and less risky for beginner investors who will be able to test the waters before diving in this speculative market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Besides capital management, HYIPs also offer commissions to members who are able to bring more customers (investors) to participate in the scheme.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That is why many critics have linked HYIPs to Ponzi schemes, where money gathered from new investors are used to pay profits made by current investors. In this sense, Ponzi schemes or any thing similar to pyramid schemes are considered to be illegal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In spite of what the critics say, many experts believe HYIPs are not Ponzi schemes. Investors need to be careful about where they invest their money. Without due diligence from the investor&rsquo;s side, they could easily get scammed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Read our&nbsp;<a href="http://sharehyip.com/blog">blog</a>&nbsp;to learn more HYIP tips and tricks.</p>', '2014-05-07 03:13:00', '2014-05-07 03:13:00'),
